<div class="col">
<div id="dnn_contentPane" class="contentPane"><div class="DnnModule DnnModule-NCSLPageTopics DnnModule-12436"><a name="12436"></a><div id="dnn_ctr12436_ContentPane" class="ContainerPane"><!-- Start_Module_12436 --><div id="dnn_ctr12436_ModuleContent" class="DNNModuleContent ModNCSLPageTopicsC">

<div class="page-topics">
<span class="related-topics">Related Topic:</span>
<a href="https://www.ncsl.org/ncsl-search-results/topics/25" id="dnn_ctr12436_View_lstPageTopics_lnkTopic_0" class="btn btn-secondary">Environment and Natural Resources</a>

</div>
</div><!-- End_Module_12436 --></div>
</div><div class="DnnModule DnnModule-2sxc DnnModule-15794 DnnVersionableControl"><a name="15794"></a><div id="dnn_ctr15794_ContentPane" class="ContainerPane"><!-- Start_Module_15794 --><div id="dnn_ctr15794_ModuleContent" class="DNNModuleContent Mod2sxcC">
<div class='sc-content-block' data-cb-instance='15794' data-cb-id='15794'>




<div class="post-item mx-md-auto mx-1 col-xxl-10 px-xxl-0 col-xl-10 mt-md-2 mt-1 my-1 contentunlimited-wrapper" >

















<div class="post-info mb-md-5 mb32 anchor-search"
>
<p>The National Conference of State Legislatures tracks environment and natural resources bills that have been introduced in the 50 states, territories and Washington, D.C. Environment and natural resources legislation broadly addresses air quality, disaster mitigation, environmental cleanup, land, wildlife, water, waste and recycling.</p> </div>
</div>

<style>
.post-info .col-xxl-10, .post-info .col-xl-10 {
width: 100%!important
}
</style>






</div>
</div><!-- End_Module_15794 --></div>
</div><div class="DnnModule DnnModule-2sxc DnnModule-27102 DnnVersionableControl"><a name="27102"></a><div id="dnn_ctr27102_ContentPane" class="ContainerPane"><!-- Start_Module_27102 --><div id="dnn_ctr27102_ModuleContent" class="DNNModuleContent Mod2sxcC">
<div class='sc-content-block' data-cb-instance='27102' data-cb-id='27102'>







<div class="post-item mx-md-auto mx-1 col-xxl-10 px-xxl-0 col-xl-10 mt-md-2 mt-1 my-1 Tool Card-wrapper" >
















<ul class="list-unstyled tab-tool mb-5 row-eq-height ToolCard" id="ToolCard-51319">





<li id="51319" class="tab-tool--item"

















>
<a href="https://www.ncsl.org/environment-and-natural-resources/environment-and-natural-resources-legislation-database" target="_self" class="tab-link">
<i class="tab-tool--icon icon-tool-database" aria-hidden="true"></i><span class="visually-hidden">NCSL on </span>
<div class="tab-tool--text">


<span class="tab-tool--title">Environment Legislation Database</span>

<div class="tab-tool--description">2023-present</div>
</div>
</a>

</li>

</div><div class="DnnModule DnnModule-2sxc DnnModule-8808 DnnVersionableControl"><a name="8808"></a><div id="dnn_ctr8808_ContentPane" class="ContainerPane"><!-- Start_Module_8808 --><div id="dnn_ctr8808_ModuleContent" class="DNNModuleContent Mod2sxcC">
<div class='sc-content-block' data-cb-instance='8808' data-cb-id='8808'>






<div class="post-item mx-md-auto mx-1 col-xxl-10 px-xxl-0 col-xl-10 mt-md-2 mt-1 my-1 readmore-wrapper" >


















<div id="10204" class="read-more-wrap anchor-search" >

<div id="toggleContent-10204" class="cutoff-text"

















>
<h2>Database Notes</h2>
<ul>
<li>You can search legislation for each year from 2009 to 2022 by state, topic, keyword, year, status or primary sponsor. Please note: Some issues were added to the database after 2009, so historical data may vary by issue area.</li>
<li>Bills may appear twice in&nbsp;carry over states. In these states, please check the last date of action to ensure the status of the bill reflects the appropriate year.&nbsp;</li>
<li>For current legislation in related policy areas, see NCSL&rsquo;s <a href="/environment-and-natural-resources/state-bill-tracking-database" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Environment and Natural Resources State Bill Tracking Database</a> and <a href="/energy/energy-state-bill-tracking-database" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Energy State Bill Tracking Database</a>.</li>
<li>Clicking on the bill number displays the full text of bills (for bills from 2015 and later).</li>
</ul>
<div class='' ><div class='sc-content-block' data-cb-instance='8808' data-cb-id='-10243'>






<div class="post-item mx-md-auto mx-1 col-xxl-10 px-xxl-0 col-xl-10 mt-md-2 mt-1 my-1 glossary-wrapper" >
















<div class=" bg-box list-wrapper glossary">



<div class="glossary text-center"

















>

<h3>Explanation of Search Keywords</h3>
</div>


<ul class="anchor-search list-unstyled list-glossary ms-0">

<li lang="en" class="list-glossary--item entity-10246"

















>
<h4 class="list-glossary--item--title">Air Quality (Outdoor)</h4>
<span class="list-glossary--item--text item-text">
<p>Legislation related to national ambient air quality standards (NAAQS), ground-level ozone and vehicle emissions (for legislation on methane emissions and emissions related to energy production, see the <a href="/energy/energy-state-bill-tracking-database">Energy Database</a>).</p>
</span>
</li>
<li lang="en" class="list-glossary--item entity-10246"

















>
<h4 class="list-glossary--item--title">Disaster Mitigation</h4>
<span class="list-glossary--item--text item-text">
<p>Legislation related to state efforts to reduce the impact of natural disasters including building codes and land use - includes appropriations bills.</p>
</span>
</li>
<li lang="en" class="list-glossary--item entity-10246"

















>
<h4 class="list-glossary--item--title">Disaster Mitigation-Flooding</h4>
<span class="list-glossary--item--text item-text">
<p>Legislation related to flood management and flood control. Includes select funding/financing bills.</p>
</span>
</li>
<li lang="en" class="list-glossary--item entity-10246"

















>
<h4 class="list-glossary--item--title">Disaster Mitigation-High Wind</h4>
<span class="list-glossary--item--text item-text">
<p>Legislation related to tornadoes, hurricanes, nor'easters, and other high wind events.</p>
</span>
</li>
<li lang="en" class="list-glossary--item entity-10246"

















>
<h4 class="list-glossary--item--title">Disaster Mitigation-Seismic</h4>
<span class="list-glossary--item--text item-text">
<p>Legislation related to the structural integrity of buildings, seismic hazard mapping and seismic safety (non-oil and gas related).</p>
</span>
</li>
<li lang="en" class="list-glossary--item entity-10246"

















>
<h4 class="list-glossary--item--title">Disaster Mitigation-Wildfire</h4>
<span class="list-glossary--item--text item-text">
<p>Legislation related to wildfire mitigation efforts &ndash; includes select financing/appropriations bills.</p>
</span>
</li>
<li lang="en" class="list-glossary--item entity-10246"

















>
<h4 class="list-glossary--item--title">Environmental Cleanup</h4>
<span class="list-glossary--item--text item-text">
<p>Legislation related to state environmental cleanup programs and activities, such as Superfund sites federal facilities, brownfields, oil spills, and hazardous waste management facilities with a spill or release. This tag does not include most bills specific to air pollutants or water cleanup.</p>
</span>
</li>
<li lang="en" class="list-glossary--item entity-10246"

















>
<h4 class="list-glossary--item--title">Land</h4>
<span class="list-glossary--item--text item-text">
<p>Legislation related to the use and management of land, both generally and including the sub-categories below.</p>
</span>
</li>
<li lang="en" class="list-glossary--item entity-10246"

















>
<h4 class="list-glossary--item--title">Land-Conservation Easements</h4>
<span class="list-glossary--item--text item-text">
<p>Legislation related to the creation, monitoring, enforcement and incentives for conservation easements&mdash;voluntary legal agreements between landowners and eligible organizations or government agencies that limit uses of land to protect certain values (environmental, historical, agricultural, etc.)</p>
</span>
</li>
<li lang="en" class="list-glossary--item entity-10246"

















>
<h4 class="list-glossary--item--title">Land-Forests</h4>
<span class="list-glossary--item--text item-text">
<p>Legislation related to the health and management of forests, including carbon sequestration and storage, biomass, prescribed fire and the timber industry.</p>
</span>
</li>
<li lang="en" class="list-glossary--item entity-10246"

















>
<h4 class="list-glossary--item--title">Land-State Parks</h4>
<span class="list-glossary--item--text item-text">
<p>Legislation related to the use, management and administration of state parks systems. Also includes bills on state offices of outdoor recreation.</p>
</span>
</li>
<li lang="en" class="list-glossary--item entity-10246"

















>
<h4 class="list-glossary--item--title">Waste and Recycling</h4>
<span class="list-glossary--item--text item-text">
<p>Legislation related to the collection, processing and management of solid waste, recyclables and organics, both generally and including the sub-categories below.</p>
</span>
</li>
<li lang="en" class="list-glossary--item entity-10246"

















>
<h4 class="list-glossary--item--title">Waste and Recycling-Beverage Containers</h4>
<span class="list-glossary--item--text item-text">
<p>Legislation related to beverage container deposit programs sometimes referred to as &ldquo;bottle bills.&rdquo;</p>
</span>
</li>
<li lang="en" class="list-glossary--item entity-10246"

















>
<h4 class="list-glossary--item--title">Waste and Recycling-Composting</h4>
<span class="list-glossary--item--text item-text">
<p>Legislation related to the decomposition of organic material, including food scraps and yard debris. Also includes bills prescribing other means to reduce food waste, such as donations, tax incentives and date labeling.</p>
</span>
</li>
<li lang="en" class="list-glossary--item entity-10246"

















>
<h4 class="list-glossary--item--title">Waste and Recycling-Electronic</h4>
<span class="list-glossary--item--text item-text">
<p>Legislation related to the recovery and recycling of used electronic equipment, including mobile phones, computers, televisions, etc.</p>
</span>
</li>
<li lang="en" class="list-glossary--item entity-10246"

















>
<h4 class="list-glossary--item--title">Waste and Recycling-Plastic</h4>
<span class="list-glossary--item--text item-text">
<p>Legislation related to the use of various plastics products, including bags (bans, fees, recycling), straws, polystyrene, and other packaging. Also includes bills on paper bags.</p>
</span>
</li>
<li lang="en" class="list-glossary--item entity-10246"

















>
<h4 class="list-glossary--item--title">Waste – Nuclear & Radioactive</h4>
<span class="list-glossary--item--text item-text">
<p>Legislation related to the siting and disposal of radioactive waste, specifically, TRU waste, High-Level Radioactive Waste and Spent Nuclear Fuel.</p>
</span>
</li>
<li lang="en" class="list-glossary--item entity-10246"

















>
<h4 class="list-glossary--item--title">Water - Conservation & Efficiency</h4>
<span class="list-glossary--item--text item-text">
<p>Legislation related to efficient use of water resources by various users, such as industry, residential, state-owned facilities and agriculture. Bills address topics such as plumbing fixtures, rainwater harvesting, xeriscaping and other conservation approaches. See NCSL&rsquo;s <a href="/environment-and-natural-resources/environmental-health-state-bill-tracking-database">Environmental Health Database</a> for drinking water, wastewater and other water policy bills.</p>
</span>
</li>
<li lang="en" class="list-glossary--item entity-10246"

















>
<h4 class="list-glossary--item--title">Water – Resources & Planning</h4>
<span class="list-glossary--item--text item-text">
<p>Legislation related to state, regional and local water supply planning processes. These bills focus primarily on the quantity of water for various users and may address source water protection, infrastructure projects, and other broader supply topics. These bills do not relate to drinking water regulations. See NCSL&rsquo;s <a href="/environment-and-natural-resources/environmental-health-state-bill-tracking-database">Environmental Health Database</a> for drinking water, wastewater and other water policy bills.</p>
</span>
</li>
<li lang="en" class="list-glossary--item entity-10246"

















>
<h4 class="list-glossary--item--title">Wildlife</h4>
<span class="list-glossary--item--text item-text">
<p>Legislation related to various protected and invasive species, pollinators, habitat restoration and wildlife trafficking. Does not include bills on hunting and fishing at this time.</p>
</span>
</li>
<li lang="en" class="list-glossary--item entity-10246"

















>
<h4 class="list-glossary--item--title">Wildlife – Invasive Species</h4>
<span class="list-glossary--item--text item-text">
<p>Legislation related to non-native species that cause or are likely to cause harm to human health or the environment, including both plants and animals (aquatic and terrestrial).</p>
</span>
</li>
<li lang="en" class="list-glossary--item entity-10246"

















>
<h4 class="list-glossary--item--title">Wildlife – Pollinators</h4>
<span class="list-glossary--item--text item-text">
<p>Legislation related to animals (primarily insects) that fertilize flowering plants and crops. Includes bills to improve pollinator health through research, habitat protection, reducing pesticides, and support of the beekeeping industry.</p>
</span>
</li>

</ul>
</div>

</div>









<link rel="stylesheet" href="/Portals/0/2sxc/NCSL/styles/dist/lists.css" data-enableoptimizations='true:footer' />



</div></div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</div>

<script>
// Define a regular expression that matches the opening and closing tags of an HTML element
var regex = /<([a-z][a-z0-9]*)\b[^>]*>(.*?)<\/\1>/i;
var sections = document.querySelectorAll('#toggleContent-10204');
var start = 175; // number of words before we add a Read More toggle

sections.forEach(function (section) {

// remove html so we can chack for # of words
var result = section.innerHTML.replace(regex, "");
var words = result.split(" ").length;
var secondPart = section.innerHTML.substring(start, words);
var updatedSecondPart = secondPart.replace(regex, (match, p1, p2) => {
// Return the original matched element, plus the additional div element
return `${match}<span id="has-expanded-text"> </span>`;
});

// Replace the original second part of the string with the updated version
var updatedHtmlString = section.innerHTML.replace(secondPart, updatedSecondPart);
// Update with new strng that includes has-expanded-text element (element used to trigger read more to open on page load when content is inside red more)
if ((words > start)) {
section.innerHTML = updatedHtmlString;
}
function removeRead() {
var item = document.getElementById("10204");
var element = document.getElementById("togglebtn-10204");

item.removeChild(element);
item.classList.add('hide-before');
}
if(("False" !== "True") && (words < start)) {
// Hide Read More button if words are less than 200 ...
removeRead();
}
})

// if anchor is inside of collapsed text we need to open up
$(function () {

$(document).on('click', 'a[href^="#"]', function (ev) {
var targetId = $(ev.target).attr('href'),
$target = $(targetId)

if ($target.parents('.cutoff-text').find('.has-expanded-text').length == 0) {
console.log('hello');
$target.parents('.cutoff-text').addClass('expanded');
$target.parents('.read-more-wrap').children('.toggle-more').addClass('icon-remove expanded').removeClass('icon-add').text('Show Less');
};


});

})

<b>Status:</b>
Enacted - Act No. 2018-147
<br />
<b>Date of Last Action:</b>
03/01/2018 - Enacted
<br />
<b>Author:</b>
Drake D (R)<b> Additional Authors: </b>Carns (R);Shedd (R);Polizos (R);Wilcox (R);Ingram (R);Williams Ja (R);Fincher (R);Crawford (R);Lovvorn (R);Standridge (R);Butler (R);Hurst (R);Sanderford (R);Greer (R);Wood (R);McCutcheon (R);Brown (R);Nordgren (R);Weaver (R);Ellis (R)
<br />
<b>Topics: </b>
Land, Land-State Parks
<br />
<b>Summary: </b>
Creates the Park for Patriots Act of 2018, relates to State Park entry without charge for military personnel on holidays, provides that all Alabama residents who are active and retired members in good standing of the United States Armed Forces or National Guard, including all reserve components thereof, free admission to any State Park operated by the Department of Conservation and Natural Resources on all days wherein entry to such State Park is open to the general public, including on a holiday.

1/9/2018
<br />

Orr (R)
<br />
<b>Topics: </b>
<br />
<b>Summary: </b>
Relates to gasoline and diesel fuel taxation, authorizes a county commission to call for a referendum on the levy of an excise tax on gasoline and diesel fuel not to exceed a certain amount per gallon for specific road and bridge projects identified by the county prior to the referendum, provides that the excise tax could only be in effect for a period not to exceed a certain time period, provides for subsequent local referendums asking that new levies be authorized.

Proposes an amendment to the Constitution of Alabama of 1901, to provide that the Forever Wild Land Trust may not acquire property in a county having a population of 20,000 or less if the property held by the trust in the county exceeds or will exceed 11,000 Acres unless the purchase of the property by the Forever Wild Land Trust is approved by the county commission of the county.
<br />

Baker A (R)
<br />
<b>Topics: </b>

AL H 543<br />

</div>
<div style="font-weight: bold;">
Wastewater Regulation<br />
</div>
<b>Status:</b>
Enacted - Act No. 2009-773
<br />
<b>Date of Last Action:</b>
05/22/2009 - Enacted
<br />
<b>Author:</b>
Grantland (D)
<br />
<b>Topics: </b>
Water-Conservation/Efficiency
<br />
<b>Summary: </b>
Relates to the regulation of wastewater onsite management entities, provides for the management of privately owned wastewater systems by wastewater management entities, provides requirements and procedures for the establishment of regulated entities for the operation and management of wastewater systems, assures financial stability and the continued viability of wastewater management entities through regulation by the Public Service Commission, provides for new certification, permitting and regulatory fees.

$(document).ready(function () {
$(".clickForHistory").click(function () {
$(this).nextAll('div[class="historyList"]').eq(0).slideToggle(100);
});
$("#btnShowAllHistory").click(function () {
$(".historyList").show();
return false;
});
$("#btnHideAllHistory").click(function () {
$(".historyList").hide();
return false;
});

var selectAllTopics = $('#dnn_ctr15746_StateNetDB_ckBxAllTopics');
selectAllTopics.click(function () {
$("#dnn_ctr15746_StateNetDB_ckBxTopics input[type='checkbox']").attr('checked', selectAllTopics.is(':checked'));
});

$("#btnClearAllTopics").click(function () {
$("#dnn_ctr15746_StateNetDB_ckBxTopics input[type='checkbox']").attr('checked', false);
selectAllTopics.removeAttr('checked');
});

var topicsClick = $('#dnn_ctr15746_StateNetDB_ckBxTopics');
topicsClick.click(function () {
selectAllTopics.removeAttr('checked');
});

var selectAllStates = $('#dnn_ctr15746_StateNetDB_ckBxAllStates');
selectAllStates.click(function () {
$("#dnn_ctr15746_StateNetDB_ckBxStates input[type='checkbox']").attr('checked', selectAllStates.is(':checked'));
});

$("#btnClearAllStates").click(function () {
$("#dnn_ctr15746_StateNetDB_ckBxStates input[type='checkbox']").attr('checked', false);
selectAllStates.removeAttr('checked');
});

var statesClick = $('#dnn_ctr15746_StateNetDB_ckBxStates');
statesClick.click(function () {
selectAllStates.removeAttr('checked');
});
});

function PrintResults() {
var filter = document.getElementById("dnn_ctr15746_StateNetDB_divSearchFilter");
var resultHeader = document.getElementById("dnn_ctr15746_StateNetDB_resultsHeader");
var resultCount = document.getElementById("dnn_ctr15746_StateNetDB_resultsCount");
var resultsContent = document.getElementById("dnn_ctr15746_StateNetDB_linkList");
var printscreen = window.open('', '', 'left=100,top=100,width=600,height=600');
printscreen.document.write('<html><head><title>Search Results</title>');
printscreen.document.write('</head><body>');
printscreen.document.write(filter.innerHTML);
printscreen.document.write('<br/><b>');
printscreen.document.write(resultHeader.innerHTML);
printscreen.document.write(' - ');
printscreen.document.write(resultCount.innerHTML);
printscreen.document.write('<br/><br/>');
printscreen.document.write('</b>');
printscreen.document.write(resultsContent.innerHTML);
printscreen.document.write('<img src="../DesktopModules/NCSLStateNet/Images/statenet.png" id="dnn_ctr15746_StateNetDB_statenet" alt="statenet" class="img" />');
printscreen.document.write('</body></html>');
printscreen.document.close();
printscreen.focus();
printscreen.print();
printscreen.close();
return false;
}

$(document).ready(function () {

<script>
const ncslResultsSearchUrl = '';

function ncslUpdateSearch(offset=null) {
let url = ncslResultsSearchUrl;

if (offset == null) {
offset = _searchParams.offset;
}

url += '&searchText=' + encodeURIComponent(_searchParams.searchText);

var topics = ncslGetSelected('search-results-list-topics');
var policies = ncslGetSelected('search-results-list-policies');
var resources = ncslGetSelected('search-results-list-resources');

url += '&topics=' + topics.join(",");
url += '&policies=' + policies.join(",");
url += '&resources=' + resources.join(",");

url += '&sortOrder=' + _searchParams.sortOrder;
url += '&sortBy=' + _searchParams.sortBy;
url += '&offset=' + offset;

url += '&dateStart=' + encodeURIComponent($('#resultsDateRangeStart').val());
url += '&dateEnd=' + encodeURIComponent($('#resultsDateRangeEnd').val());

url += '&t=' + (new Date()).getTime(); //cache busting

$.get(url,
function (data, status) {
$('#ncslResultsContainer').html(data);
window.scrollTo({ top: 0, behavior: 'smooth' });
});
}

function hookupCBEvents(tableClass) {
const $table = $('.' + tableClass);
$('td input:checkbox', $table).change(e => {
ncslUpdateSearch();
});
}

function ncslGetSelected(tableClass) {
const values = [];

const $table = $('.' + tableClass);
$('td input:checked', $table).each(function () {
values.push(this.value);
});

return values;
}

function sortResults(sortBy, sortOrder) {
console.log({ sortBy, sortOrder });
_searchParams.sortBy = sortBy;
_searchParams.sortOrder = sortOrder;
ncslUpdateSearch();
}

$(document).ready(function () {
$('.datepicker').datepicker({
orientation: 'top right'
});

applySearchParamsToUI();

$('#resultsDateRangeStart').change(e => {
ncslUpdateSearch();
});

$('#resultsDateRangeEnd').change(e => {
ncslUpdateSearch();
});

hookupCBEvents('search-results-list-topics');
hookupCBEvents('search-results-list-policies');
hookupCBEvents('search-results-list-resources');

});
</script>
</div>


<script>
//SHARED functions (may be called from the search bar or the results)
var _searchParams = {};

function applySearchParamsToUI() {
//This field comes back with the search results
const searchParamsJSON = $('#fldSearchParams').val();

if (searchParamsJSON) {
_searchParams = JSON.parse(searchParamsJSON);

$('#ncslSearchInput').val(_searchParams.searchText);

ncslApplySelected('search-results-list-topics', _searchParams.topics);
ncslApplySelected('search-results-list-policies', _searchParams.policies);
ncslApplySelected('search-results-list-resources', _searchParams.resources);

for (let id of _searchParams.topics) {
$('option[value=' + id + ']', $('#ddlTopics')).prop('selected', true);
}
$('#ddlTopics').multiselect('refresh');
}
}

//Clear all checkboxes and select the ones in the values list
function ncslApplySelected(tableClass, values) {
let $table = $('.' + tableClass);
$('td input:checkbox', $table).prop('checked', false);

for (let id of values) {
$('td input:checkbox[value=' + id + ']', $table).prop('checked', 'true');
}
}

</script>
